str2TitleCase()

Description
    string str2TitleCase(string $str)
    Attempts to properly capitalize post titles.

Parameters
    str
    The string value to modify.

Return Values
    Returns a string value with the appropriate substitutions made.
    
Examples
    <?php
	...
	if (file_exists($path ."/.breadCrumbs")) {
	$lines = file($path ."/.breadCrumbs");
	$trailArray[] = '<a href="'.$href.'" class="breadCrumbLink">'.(($str2upper === TRUE)?str2TitleCase($lines[0]):$lines[0]).'</a>';
	}
	...
    ?>

See Also
    nv_title_skip_dotted
